---
title: Wasabi Soy Chicken with Ponzu Roasted Carrots & Ginger Rice
description: Wasabi may be better known as the green spicy stuff that comes with sushi, but it can be used in so many other ways. Here, it’s blended into a mixture of sweet soy glaze, ginger, and lime juice, creating a sauce for chicken that’s equal parts tangy, aromatic, and exhilarating. The chicken is served with buttery rice and a side of roasted carrots tossed with citrusy ponzu. Dinner winner? We think so.
